Area Content Review Checklist
==============================

General
-------
__ All text has a consistent syntactic style.
__ All text is free of typos or grammatical errors.
__ Low level of repetitiveness in descriptions.
__ Descriptions are not subjective to the player's thoughts or experience.
__ Descriptions are not explanatory.
__ Long descs are readable prose of sufficient detail.
__ Obnoxious/hard to read color combinations are not used.

Overall for the area
--------------------
__ Area as a whole has a consistent thematic feel.
__ Rooms should map consistently within an area.

Rooms
-----
__ All rooms must set: light, terrain, long and short.
__ Terrain must set ALL applicable types.
__ Long desc does not describe items which can be removed.
__ Actions have reasonable syntax or hints.
__ Nouns in the long desc for present objects have add_looks.
__ Add_looks should have alternate target keys where appropriate.
__ Add_looks and triggers are complete sentences.
__ Extra settings should make sense. (e.g. no_teleport)

Naming (monsters, objects)
--------------------------
__ Proper names in name, alias and short settings are first letter capped.
__ All other words in name, alias amd short settings are lowercase.
__ Name, alias and short settings DO NOT start with articles.
__ Aliases exist for reasonable variations of the short desc.

Monsters
--------
__ Monsters must set: name, long, short, size, level, alignment(al)
                      race, gender.
__ Long desc does not describe items which can be removed.
__ Settings are consistent with the description of the monster.
__ Monster level is reasonable given it's desc.

Objects/Loot
------------
__ Items must set: name, long, short, material, weight, value.
__ Armors must also set: new_type, quality, warmth.
__ Weapons must also set: new_type, quality, material_composition.
__ Settings are consistent with the description of the object.
__ Actions have reasonable syntax or hints.


